  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is the best online Android app development course?",
  "response": "Selecting the best online Android app development course depends on your current skill level, learning style, and goals. Here are some highly recommended courses that cater to different audiences:\n\n---\n\n### **For Beginners:**\n1. **Android App Development by Google (Udacity)**\n   - **Platform:** Udacity\n   - **Description:** This free course, developed by Google, introduces Android app development using Kotlin. It covers the basics of Android Studio, UI design, and app architecture.\n   - **Best For:** Complete beginners with no prior Android development experience.\n   - **Link:** [Udacity Android Development](https://www.udacity.com/course/new-android-fundamentals--ud851)\n\n2. **The Complete Android 12 & Kotlin Development Masterclass**\n   - **Platform:** Udemy\n   - **Description:** Taught by Denis Panjuta, this course covers Android app development from scratch using Kotlin. It includes hands-on projects and up-to-date Android features.\n   - **Best For:** Beginners and intermediate learners.\n   - **Link:** [Udemy Android Kotlin Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/android-kotlin-developer/)\n\n---\n\n### **For Intermediate Learners:**\n3. **Developing Android Apps with Kotlin (Google)**\n   - **Platform:** Udacity\n   - **Description:** This course delves deeper into Android development, focusing on app architecture, navigation, and testing.\n   - **Best For:** Those with basic Android knowledge looking to advance their skills.\n   - **Link:** [Udacity Kotlin for Android](https://www.udacity.com/course/developing-android-apps-with-kotlin--ud9012)\n\n4. **Master Android App Development with Kotlin**\n   - **Platform:** Coursera (by Meta)\n   - **Description:** This course teaches Android app development using Kotlin and focuses on building real-world applications.\n   - **Best For:** Intermediate learners.\n   - **Link:** [Coursera Android Development](https://www.coursera.org/learn/meta-android-app-developer-kotlin)\n\n---\n\n### **For Advanced Learners:**\n5. **Advanced Android App Development by Google (Udacity)**\n   - **Platform:** Udacity\n   - **Description:** This course focuses on advanced topics like app security, performance optimization, and custom views.\n   - **Best For:** Experienced Android developers.\n   - **Link:** [Udacity Advanced Android](https://www.udacity.com/course/advanced-android-app-development--ud855)\n\n6. **Android Jetpack Compose: The Comprehensive Bootcamp**\n   - **Platform:** Udemy\n   - **Description:** Learn Jetpack Compose, the modern UI toolkit for Android, with this in-depth course.\n   - **Best For:** Developers looking to stay updated with the latest Android technologies.\n   - **Link:** [Udemy Jetpack Compose Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/android-jetpack-compose/)\n\n---\n\n### **Other Recommendations:**\n- **Codecademy: Learn Android Development**\n  - **Platform:** Codecademy\n  - **Description:** A beginner-friendly course that teaches Android development using Java and Kotlin.\n  - **Link:** [Codecademy Android Development](https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-android)\n\n- **Pluralsight: Android Development**\n  - **Platform:** Pluralsight\n  - **Description:** Offers a variety of courses for different skill levels, from beginner to advanced.\n  - **Link:** [Pluralsight Android Development](https://www.pluralsight.com/browse/software-development/mobile-app-development/android)\n\n---\n\n### **Key Considerations:**\n- **Language:** Choose a course that teaches Kotlin, as it is the modern and preferred language for Android development.\n- **Hands-On Projects:** Look for courses with practical projects to build a portfolio.\n- **Instructor Quality:** Check reviews and instructor credentials.\n- **Cost:** Some platforms like Udacity and Coursera offer free courses, while others like Udemy and Pluralsight require payment.\n\nUltimately, the best course is the one that aligns with your learning goals and preferred teaching style!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
